<module status="bronze">
    <h>ais</h>
    <p><g>ais</g> is a (fossilised) noun.</p>
    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section>
            <h>complement</h>
            <module status="bronze">
                <h>air ais</h>
                <p><g><a href="?gd=air">air</a> ais</g>
                    <en>back, backwards</en> is a prepositional compound.</p>
                <section>
                    <h>uses</h>
                    <section>
                        <h>complement</h>
                        <module status="bronze" id="rach_air_ais">
                            <h>rach air ais</h>
                            <p><g><a href="?gd=rach">rach</a> air ais</g>
                                <en>go back(wards), recede, regress, reverse</en> – <ul>
                                    <li>pedagogical examples – <xl id="rach_air_ais-pedag">
                                            <li>
                                                <gd>Thèid mi <m>air ais</m> don talla. | An rachadh
                                                  tu <m>air ais</m> a-rithist? | Chaidh e air ais. </gd>
                                                <tr>I’ll go back to the hall. | Would you go back
                                                  again? | He went back.</tr>
                                                <ref text="601">td. 476, 477, 478</ref>
                                            </li>
                                        </xl>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </p>
                        </module>
                    </section>
                </section>

                <p>Examples from Gairm – <xl id="gairm">
                        <li>
                            <gd>Ma rannsaicheas sinn <m>air ais</m> fada gu leòir chì sinn nach robh
                                sgoilean anns an Oban gus an ochdamh linn deug. Bha an sgoil bheag a
                                b’ fhaisge air anns a’ Chill Mhóir cóig mìle air falbh, agus tha e
                                coltach gu robh an sgoil sin air an fheadhainn bu shine an
                                Earra-Ghaidheal.</gd>
                            <tr>If we research back long enough we will see that there were no
                                schools in Oban until the eighteenth century. The closest little
                                school was in Kilmore five miles away, and it appears that that
                                school was one of the oldest in Argyll.</tr>
                            <ref text="400-20">td. 363</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </module>
        </section>
    </section>




</module>
